Statistical Tests

StatisticalTests.Rmd
library(umncvmstats)
mtcars <- datasets::mtcars |> 
  dplyr::mutate(dplyr::across(c(cyl, vs, am, gear, carb), forcats::as_factor)) |>
  dplyr::mutate(vs=forcats::fct_recode(vs, "V-shaped"="0", "straight"="1"),
                am=forcats::fct_recode(am, "automatic"="0", manual="1"))

Tests for Proportions

One Proportion Test 

one_proportion_test(vs~1, data=mtcars)
response response.value x n proportion conf.low conf.high
vs straight 14  32  0.44 0.28 0.61
Wilson's proportion test (two.sided), with 95% confidence intervals.

Separately by another categorical variable 

one_proportion_test(vs ~ am, data=mtcars)
vs ~ am
vs am x n proportion conf.low conf.high
straight automatic 7  19  0.37 0.19 0.59
straight manual 7  13  0.54 0.29 0.77
Wilson's proportion test (two.sided), with 95% confidence intervals.

Two Proportion Test 

two_proportion_test(vs ~ am, data=mtcars)
vs ~ am
vs am proportion conf.low conf.high chisq.value p.value
straight automatic - manual −0.17 −0.24 0.58 0.35   0.56
2-sample test for equality of proportions with continuity correction (two.sided), with 95% confidence intervals.

together in one table 

combine_tests(
  one_proportion_test(vs ~ am, data=mtcars),
  two_proportion_test(vs ~ am, data=mtcars))

Paired Proportion Test (McNemar’s) 

set.seed(15)
testing <- tidyr::tibble(before=rep(c("fail","pass"),c(20,30)),
                   after=rep(c("fail", "pass", "fail", "pass"), c(5,15,5,25)))
xtabs(~before+after, data=testing) |> addmargins()
#>       after
#> before fail pass Sum
#>   fail    5   15  20
#>   pass    5   25  30
#>   Sum    10   40  50

combine_tests(
  one_proportion_test(before+after~1, data=testing),
  paired_proportion_test(after - before ~ 1, data=testing))
response response.value x n proportion conf.low conf.high null chisq.value p.value footnote
before pass 30  50  0.60 0.46 0.72


1 
after pass 40  50  0.80 0.67 0.89


1 
after - before pass 15  20  0.75

0.50 5.0   0.025 2 
1 Wilson's proportion test (two.sided), with 95% confidence intervals.
2 McNemar's test, using Wilson's proportion test (two.sided).

Paired t-test 

set.seed(15)
testing <- tidyr::tibble(before=rnorm(50, mean=80, sd=7),
                         after=rnorm(50, mean=85, sd=7))

combine_tests(
  one_t_test(before+after~1, data=testing),
  paired_t_test(after - before ~ 1, data=testing))
